oreign units in Denmark:\n\nTop Danish officials told General Gruenther during his visit to Copenhagen that their country could not accept an offer to station foreign NATO air units in Denmark in peacetime.\n\nGruenther comments that this decision will substantially reduce NATO military capabilities in northern Europe, and that SHAPE military planning will have to be revised. He believes that as far as military effectiveness is concerned, there is no satisfactory alternative.\n\nComment: The American embassy in Copenhagen had believed that Denmark might agree at least to the temporary stationing of American air units in the country.\n\nThe Danish decision may adversely influence Norway's attitude on the question of stationing NATO units in that country during peaceti", "token_count": 123, "token_end_0based": 250, "token_start_0based": 128, "token_text": "9 copenhagen rejects peacetime stationing of foreign units in denmark top danish officials told general gruenther during his visit to copenhagen that their country could not accept an offer to station foreign nato air units in denmark in peacetime gruenther comments that this decision will substantially reduce nato military capabilities in northern europe and that shape military planning will have to be revised he believes that as far as military effectiveness is concerned there is no satisfactory alternative comment the american embassy in copenhagen had believed that denmark might agree at least to the temporary stationing of american air units in the country the danish decision may adversely influence norway's attitude on the question of stationing nato units in that country during peacetime", "unred_source_page": 7}
